<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>My Page</title>
<style>
<!-- For class attribute we start with .-->
  .box {
    color : red;
  }
  <!-- for id attribute we start with # -->
  #box2 {
    color : blue;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<!-- Here is an examples of self closing tags -->
This is self closing <br> tag
<p style="color:red">This is inline style, text will be displayed in red</p>
<p class="box">This text will be displayed in red</p>
<p id="box2"> this text will displayed in blue </p>
<p class="box"> with the help of class attribute we can add styles to one or more tags but it is not possible in case of id</p>
</body>
</html>
